ectionProvider. Finally, it's crucial that I can assert certain behaviors when using getName and getChildCount methods.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Navigating serialization with native image**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether `ObjectStreamClass.newInstance` will cause the fields to be null, which would result in `getChildCount` returning 0. For the native image scenario, if this method is reflected, it instantiates an XppDom, so do I need metadata for its serialization? I should adjust the build.gradle to include necessary opening arguments and ensure patterns are consistent without manually writing metadata. I wonder if using `--add-opens=java.base/java.io=ALL-UNNAMED` will work for accessing private constructors in the native image. Finally, I need to watch out for raw type warnings when compiling my tests.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Z3T4pDH8vpysuqHud61lvkKL|fc_045a421a425e7438016a258126ca60819687c156beeb159175", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/src/test/java/com_thoughtworks_xstream/xstream/PureJavaReflectionProviderTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage com_thoughtworks_xstream.xstream;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport com.thoughtworks.xstream.converters.reflection.PureJavaReflectionProvider;\nimport com.thoughtworks.xstream.io.xml.xppdom.XppDom;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class PureJavaReflectionProviderTest {\n    @Test\n    void createsTypeWithDefaultConstructor() {\n        PureJavaReflectionProvider provider = new PureJavaReflectionProvider();\n\n        Object instance = provider.newInstance(PureJavaReflectionProvider.class);\n\n        assertThat(instance).isInstanceOf(PureJavaReflectionProvider.class);\n        assertThat(instance).isNotSameAs(provider);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void createsSerializableTypeWithoutDefaultConstructor() {\n        PureJavaReflectionProvider provider = new PureJavaReflectionProvider();\n\n        Object instance = provider.newInstance(XppDom.class);\n\n        assertThat(instance).isInstanceOf(XppDom.class);\n        XppDom dom = (XppDom)instance;\n        assertThat(dom.getName()).isNull();\n        assertThat(dom.getChildCount()).isZero();\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1220, "output": 1400, "cacheRead": 53760, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 56380, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780842763958, "responseId": "resp_045a421a425e7438016a25810c9b888196952a46efa8b59ce3"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_Z3T4pDH8vpysuqHud61lvkKL|fc_045a421a425e7438016a258126ca60819687c156beeb159175", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 1294 bytes to tests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/src/test/java/com_thoughtworks_xstream/xstream/PureJavaReflectionProviderTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1780842791947}]}
