 need to search more efficiently for the right one. I also have concerns about Python's regex—it feels flawed for this purpose. Should I consider using bytecode instead? But then I'm stuck on where to find the source. I really want to make this work smoothly!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating constructors**\\n\\nI’m thinking about file constructors and how they should be all public with arguments, but there shouldn’t be any no-argument constructors. If there are no-arg constructors, they might conflict with the intended design. It seems like falling back might create complications. I want to ensure that I’m making these constructors work effectively. Making this decision could simplify usage and reduce confusion, but I need to think it through.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_3eidrjLTQCBON9aFnRaTA45F|fc_045a421a425e7438016a2582c3006c8196b7aa1c6582bf1f0f", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/src/test/java/com_thoughtworks_xstream/xstream/PureJavaReflectionProviderTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport com.thoughtworks.xstream.converters.reflection.PureJavaReflectionProvider;\nimport com.thoughtworks.xstream.io.xml.xppdom.XppDom;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class PureJavaReflectionProviderTest {\n    @Test\n    void createsTypeWithDefaultConstructor() {", "newText": "import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport com.thoughtworks.xstream.converters.reflection.PureJavaReflectionProvider;\nimport com.thoughtworks.xstream.io.xml.xppdom.XppDom;\nimport java.io.File;\nimport java.lang.reflect.ReflectPermission;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.net.URLClassLoader;\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\nimport java.security.Permission;\nimport java.util.Arrays;\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class PureJavaReflectionProviderTest {\n    @Test\n    void createsTypeWithDefaultConstructor() {"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void createsSerializableTypeWithoutDefaultConstructor() {\n        PureJavaReflectionProvider provider = new PureJavaReflectionProvider();\n\n        Object instance = provider.newInstance(XppDom.class);\n\n        assertThat(instance).isInstanceOf(XppDom.class);\n        XppDom dom = (XppDom) instance;\n        assertThat(dom.getName()).isNull();\n        assertThat(dom.getChildCount()).isZero();\n    }\n}\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void createsSerializableTypeWithoutDefaultConstructor() {\n        PureJavaReflectionProvider provider = new PureJavaReflectionProvider();\n\n        Object instance = provider.newInstance(XppDom.class);\n\n        assertThat(instance).isInstanceOf(XppDom.class);\n        XppDom dom = (XppDom) instance;\n        assertThat(dom.getName()).isNull();\n        assertThat(dom.getChildCount()).isZero();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void createsSerializableTypeWithObjectInputStreamFallback() throws Exception {\n        try (ChildFirstXStreamClassLoader classLoader = new ChildFirstXStreamClassLoader(classPathUrls())) {\n            Runnable fallbackRunner = classLoader.loadClass(SerializationFallbackRunner.class.getName())\n                    .asSubclass(Runnable.class)\n                    .getDeclaredConstructor()\n                    .newInstance();\n            runWithoutSuppressAccessChecks(fallbackRunner);\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static URL[] classPathUrls() {\n        String classPath = System.getProperty(\"java.class.path\");\n        return Arrays.stream(classPath.split(File.pathSeparator))\n                .map(Path::of)\n                .map(Path::toUri)\n                .map(uri -> {\n                    try {\n                        return uri.toURL();\n                    } catch (Exception exception) {\n                        throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"Cannot convert class path entry to URL\", exception);\n                    }\n                })\n                .toArray(URL[]::new);\n    }\n\n    @SuppressWarnings({\"deprecation\", \"removal\"})\n    private static void runWithoutSuppressAccessChecks(Runnable runner) {\n        SecurityManager original = System.getSecurityManager();\n        System.setSecurityManager(new DenySuppressAccessChecksSecurityManager());\n        try {\n            runner.run();\n        } finally {\n            System.setSecurityManager(original);\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class SerializationFallbackRunner implements Runnable {\n        @Override\n        public void run() {\n            PureJavaReflectionProvider provider = new PureJavaReflectionProvider();\n\n            Object instance = provider.newInstance(File.class);\n\n            if (!(instance instanceof File)) {\n                throw new AssertionError(\"Expected File instance, got \" + instance.getClass());\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static class ChildFirstXStreamClassLoader extends URLClassLoader {\n        ChildFirstXStreamClassLoader(URL[] urls) {\n            super(urls, PureJavaReflectionProviderTest.class.getClassLoader());\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> loadClass(String name, boolean resolve) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            synchronized (getClassLoadingLock(name)) {\n                Class<?> loadedClass = findLoadedClass(name);\n                if (loadedClass == null && isChildFirst(name)) {\n                    try {\n                        loadedClass = findClass(name);\n                    } catch (ClassNotFoundException ignored) {\n                        // Fall back to the parent for JDK and test infrastructure classes.\n                    }\n                }\n                if (loadedClass == null) {\n                    loadedClass = super.loadClass(name, false);\n                }\n                if (resolve) {\n                    resolveClass(loadedClass);\n                }\n                return loadedClass;\n            }\n        }\n\n        private static boolean isChildFirst(String name) {\n            return name.startsWith(\"com.thoughtworks.xstream.\")\n                    || name.equals(SerializationFallbackRunner.class.getName());\n        }\n    }\n\n    @SuppressWarnings({\"deprecation\", \"removal\"})\n    private static class DenySuppressAccessChecksSecurityManager extends SecurityManager {\n        @Override\n        public void checkPermission(Permission permission) {\n            if (permission instanceof ReflectPermission\n                    && \"suppressAccessChecks\".equals(permission.getName())) {\n                throw new SecurityException(\"suppressAccessChecks intentionally disabled\");\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 536, "output": 2944, "cacheRead": 74752, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 78232, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780843165262, "responseId": "resp_045a421a425e7438016a25829dfc1c8196b9a62b07f8babde6"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_3eidrjLTQCBON9aFnRaTA45F|fc_045a421a425e7438016a2582c3006c8196b7aa1c6582bf1f0f", "toolName": "edit", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully replaced 2 block(s) in tests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/src/test/java/com_thoughtworks_xstream/xstream/PureJavaReflectionProviderTest.java."}], "details": {"diff": "     ...\n   9 import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n  10 \n  11 import com.thoughtworks.xstream.converters.reflection.PureJavaReflectionProvider;\n  12 import com.thoughtworks.xstream.io.xml.xppdom.XppDom;\n+ 13 import java.io.File;\n+ 14 import java.lang.reflect.ReflectPerm