[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm noticing current JDK issues might be failing to detect process exit. I’m thinking that dynamic access coverage likely wouldn’t capture child process call sites. If the agent instrumentation isn't active in the child process, it seems ineffective. So, I’m wondering if I need to ensure we have clean, untracked metadata to address this situation better. It's crucial to clarify these points for effective instrumentation moving forward.
[thinking] 
